  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given an **odd** integer NNN. Generate an array AAA of NNN positive integers such that:\n\n\n1≤Ai≤1051\\le A_i \\le 10^51≤Ai​≤105;\nBitwise AND of each prefix array is **greater than equal to** bitwise XOR of corresponding prefix array;\nBitwise AND of each suffix array is **less than equal to** bitwise XOR of corresponding suffix array.\nIt can be proved that at least one solution exists. If multiple solutions exist, you may print any one.\n\nNote:\n\n\nFor an array length NNN, a prefix array of length iii denotes the subarray from index 111 to iii while a suffix array of length iii is the subarray from index (N−i+1)(N-i+1)(N−i+1) to index NNN.\nThe output is large, so use **fast input-output** methods.\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of a single integer NNN, the length of required array.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line, NNN space-separated integers denoting the array satisfying the given conditions.\n\n\nIt can be proved that at least one solution exists. If multiple solutions exist, you may print any one.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤T≤10001 \\leq T \\leq 10001≤T≤1000",
      "1≤N≤105,&nbsp;N1 \\leq N \\leq 10^5,\\ N1≤N≤105,&nbsp;N is odd.",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 2⋅1062\\cdot 10^62⋅106."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n1\n3\n5",
        "output": "1\n5 6 3\n7 5 7 7 3",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111: For length 111, any array in required range would satisfy all conditions.\nTest case 222: Consider the array A=[5,6,3]A = [5, 6, 3]A=[5,6,3] where all elements are in required range:\n\nPrefix arrays:\n\n[5]:[5]:[5]: bitwise and and xor would be same\n[5,6]:[5, 6]:[5,6]: 555 &\\&& 6=46 = 46=4 is greater than 5⊕6=35 \\oplus 6 = 35⊕6=3\n[5,6,3]:[5, 6, 3]:[5,6,3]: 555 &\\&& 666 &\\&& 3=03 = 03=0 is equal to 5⊕6⊕3=05 \\oplus 6 \\oplus 3 = 05⊕6⊕3=0\n\n\nSuffix arrays:\n\n[3]:[3]:[3]: bitwise and and xor would be same\n[6,3]:[6, 3]:[6,3]: 666 &\\&& 3=23 = 23=2 is less than 6⊕3=56 \\oplus 3 = 56⊕3=5\n[5,6,3]:[5, 6, 3]:[5,6,3]: 555 &\\&& 666 &\\&& 3=03 = 03=0 is equal to 5⊕6⊕3=05 \\oplus 6 \\oplus 3 = 05⊕6⊕3=0\n\n\n\nTest case 333: Consider the array A=[7,5,7,7,3]A = [7, 5, 7, 7, 3]A=[7,5,7,7,3] where all elements are in required range:\n\nPrefix arrays:\n\n[7]:[7]:[7]: bitwise and and xor would be same\n[7,5]:[7, 5]:[7,5]: 777 &\\&& 5=55 = 55=5 is greater than 7⊕5=27 \\oplus 5 = 27⊕5=2\n[7,5,7]:[7, 5, 7]:[7,5,7]: 777 &\\&& 555 &\\&& 7=57 = 57=5 is equal to 7⊕5⊕7=57 \\oplus 5 \\oplus 7 = 57⊕5⊕7=5\n[7,5,7,7]:[7, 5, 7, 7]:[7,5,7,7]: 777 &\\&& 555 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 7=57 = 57=5 is greater to 7⊕5⊕7⊕7=27 \\oplus 5 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 7 = 27⊕5⊕7⊕7=2\n[7,5,7,7,3]:[7, 5, 7, 7, 3]:[7,5,7,7,3]: 777 &\\&& 555 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 3=13 = 13=1 is equal to 7⊕5⊕7⊕7⊕3=17 \\oplus 5 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 3= 17⊕5⊕7⊕7⊕3=1\n\n\nSuffix arrays:\n\n[3]:[3]:[3]: bitwise and and xor would be same\n[7,3]:[7, 3]:[7,3]: 777 &\\&& 3=33 = 33=3 is less than 7⊕3=47 \\oplus 3 = 47⊕3=4\n[7,7,3]:[7, 7, 3]:[7,7,3]: 777 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 3=33 = 33=3 is equal to 7⊕7⊕3=37 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 3 = 37⊕7⊕3=3\n[5,7,7,3]:[5, 7, 7, 3]:[5,7,7,3]: 555 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 3=13 = 13=1 is less to 5⊕7⊕7⊕3=65 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 3 = 65⊕7⊕7⊕3=6\n[7,5,7,7,3]:[7, 5, 7, 7, 3]:[7,5,7,7,3]: 777 &\\&& 555 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 777 &\\&& 3=13 = 13=1 is equal to 7⊕5⊕7⊕7⊕3=17 \\oplus 5 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 7 \\oplus 3= 17⊕5⊕7⊕7⊕3=1"
